(registered 2013-07-11, last updated 2013-07-17)

#
# Registration template for PKCS#11 URI.
#

According to RFC 4395, Section 5.2. ("Registration Procedures") and
Section 5.4.  ("URI Scheme Registration Template"), this document
specifies the registration template for the PKCS#11 URI registration
request.

Template author: Jan Pechanec <jan.pechanec&oracle.com>

The template references sections in the following I-D:

http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-pechanec-pkcs11uri

#
# Template starts here.
#

URI scheme name: pkcs11 (see Section "PKCS#11 URI Scheme Name")

URI scheme status: provisional

URI scheme syntax: see Section "PKCS#11 URI Scheme Syntax"

URI scheme semantics: see Section "Introduction"

Encoding considerations: see Section "PKCS#11 URI Scheme Syntax"

Applications/protocols that use this URI scheme name: see Section
"Introduction"

More specifically, a list of applications we know of that already use
PKCS#11 URI according to the existing drafts follows. The list may not
be complete.

GnuTLS
	- GNU Transport Layer Security Library
	- www.gnutls.org
Gnome
	- used by gnome-keyring since version 3.3.5
	- http://developer.gnome.org/gck/3.6/gck-PKCS11-URIs.html
Solaris 11
	- for referencing keys in ZFS filesystem encryption
	- SunSSH to reference keys/certs used in the X.509 based
	  authentication
p11-kit
	- kit for unification of PKCS#11 modules
	- http://cgit.freedesktop.org/p11-glue/p11-kit
OpenSC
	- tools and libraries for smart cards
	- https://www.opensc-project.org/opensc
	- uses PKCS#11 URIs via p11-kit
OpenConnect
	- client for Cisco's AnyConnect SSL VPN
	- http://www.infradead.org/openconnect/
	- uses PKCS#11 URIs via p11-kit

Interoperability considerations: N/A

Security considerations: see Section "Security Considerations"

Contact: Jan Pechanec, Darren J. Moffat. (See "Authors' Addresses")

Author/Change Controller: Jan Pechanec, Darren J. Moffat. (See "Authors'
Addresses")

References: see Section "References"

